Piramal Healthcare Ltd. (PIHC)  fell as
much as 8.1 percent in Mumbai trading after demand for the
shares subsided on completion of the companyâ€™s buyback on March
24.  The Mumbai-based drugmaker, which sold its domestic
generic-medicine business to Abbott Laboratories for $3.7
billion in May, said on Oct. 22 it aims to buy 41.8 million
shares at 600 rupees a piece.  Piramal declined 5.1 percent to 442 rupees at 1:26 p.m. in
Mumbai. The shares have dropped 6.2 percent this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
